headline: Wingstop Expands Through Consumer Weakness While Chipotle Fights Margin Compression
summary: Chipotle Mexican Grill (NYSE: CMG) and Wingstop (Nasdaq: WING) just reported Q3 2025 earnings revealing two fast-casual chains navigating very different paths through a challenging consumer environment. Chipotle relied on modest comp sales growth and Chipotlane expansion while fighting margin pressure. Wingstop bet on aggressive unit growth to offset a 5.6% domestic same-store sales decline. ... headline: Moxies Launches Its D.C. Flagship in the Heart of the Golden Triangle
summary: Executive Chef–turned–Franchisee Brandon Thordarson leverages culinary and brand expertise to lead the Nation’s Capital debutWASHINGTON, Dec. 03, 2025 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- Moxies, the premium-casual restaurant recognized for its handcrafted dishes, signature cocktails and award-winning hospitality, will officially open its first Washington, D.C. location on Dec. 9 at 1111 20th St. NW, just south of Dupont Circle. On opening day, Moxies will welcome the public to celebrate its newest U.S. location

headline: Chipotle (CMG) Holiday Push: Evaluating Valuation After Unwrap Extra Promotion and No Kid Hungry Partnership
summary: Chipotle Mexican Grill (CMG) is kicking off the holidays with its Unwrap Extra promotion, rolling out buy one get one entrées on select December Saturdays while pairing the campaign with a charitable push supporting No Kid Hungry. See our latest analysis for Chipotle Mexican Grill. Against this backdrop, Chipotle’s 1 month share price return of 7.73% suggests a short term bounce, but the year to date share price return of minus 43% and 1 year total shareholder return of minus 43.98% show...
